Package: traceR
Title: Metadata-Driven, Reproducible Objective-to-Result Traceability for CDISC Studies
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Appsilon", "traceR", email = "vedha@appsilon.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A general, metadata-driven framework that maps clinical study
    lineage exhaustively from Objective to Endpoint to Analysis to Output
    (Tables, Figures, Listings) down to the ADaM and SDTM variables and
    Controlled Terminology that produced each result, across CDISC standards
    (USDM, ARS, ARD, ADaM, SDTM). It ingests machine-readable metadata
    (USDM study definitions, ARS Reporting Events, define.xml, and the CDISC
    Library API), assembles a typed traceability graph, validates coverage and
    detects gaps, executes standard analyses into Analysis Results Datasets
    (ARD), and emits reproducible, content-hashed traceability artifacts. The
    goal is a traceable artifact that pins an objective to its result so that
    AI-assisted automation becomes reproducible by construction.
